def plot(image, image_size, title):
    plt.imshow(np.reshape(image,image_size), cmap = plt.cm.gray)
    plt.title(title)
    ax = plt.gca()
    ax.get_xaxis().set_visible(False)
    ax.get_yaxis().set_visible(False)
    plt.show()

Finding the Eigenfaces¶

In [7]:
# Calculate matrix A and ATA
A = M
mean_face = M.mean(axis=1)
A = A - np.vstack(mean_face)

ATA = np.matmul(A.T,A)
print("Dimensions of ATA: " + str(np.shape(ATA)))
ATA = np.divide(ATA, len(ATA))

u, v = np.linalg.eigh(ATA)
print("Number of eigenvalues: " + str(len(u)))
print("Dimensions of eigenvectors: " + str(np.shape(v)))
print("Norm of a sample column: " + str(np.linalg.norm(v[:,0])))

Dimensions of ATA: (11, 11)
Number of eigenvalues: 11
Dimensions of eigenvectors: (11, 11)
Norm of a sample column: 1.0

# Sort the eigenvalues and eigenvectors in descending order
idx = np.argsort (- u )
eigen_values = u[idx]
eigen_vectors = v[:,idx]

e_face = np.matmul(A, eigen_vectors)
for i in range(len(e_face[0])):
    im = e_face[:,i]
    plt.subplot(3,4,1+i)

Reconstructing Faces¶

In [9]:
def find_w(eigenface, image, mean_face):
    w = np.zeros(len(eigenface[0]))
    difference = image - mean_face
    for i in range(len(eigenface[0])):
        w[i] = np.dot(eigenfaces[:,i], difference)
    return w

def reconstruct(eigenfaces, mean_face, image):
    w = find_w(eigenfaces, image, mean_face)
    uw = np.matmul(eigenfaces, w)
    uw = uw + mean_face
    return uw

Recognizing Faces¶

In [14]:
def find_class(image, eigenfaces, mean_face, W):
    test_w = find_w(eigenfaces, image, mean_face)
    result = W
    norms = []
    for i in range(len(W[0])):
        #result[:,i] = result[:,i] - test_w
        norms.append(np.linalg.norm(result[:,i] - test_w))
    return (np.argmin(norms), min(norms))
